organic_results.title: Patterns of satisfaction of organizational prerequisites and personal needs in university academic departments
organic_results.snippet: A study of thirty academic departments in fifteen universities was undertaken to determine the nature of the differences between those of high and low quality. The criterion of quality was based on the findings of the report of departmental ratings published by the American Council on Education (Cartter, 1966). Two other dimensions of quality were operationalized for the research--the" functional prerequisites" of Talcott Parsons and the" need hierarchy" of Abraham Maslow.
